# Enforce LF line endings for all text files on every platform.
#
# Without this, each contributor's local `core.autocrlf` decides working-tree
# line endings: a Windows checkout (autocrlf=true) gets CRLF while Linux gets
# LF. Line-ending-sensitive tests (e.g. the doc mermaid-fence and build-queue
# grammar checks) then pass on one OS and fail on the other.
#
# `text=auto` lets git detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` forces LF in the working
# tree regardless of local git config. This repo has no Windows scripts
# (.bat/.cmd/.ps1) that would need CRLF, so LF-everywhere is safe.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Common binary types — never apply line-ending normalization to these.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.zip   binary
